cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper proposes an unsupervised learning-based approach for multi-view stereo (MVS) and focuses on the computer vision task of depth estimation from multiple views. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel network architecture and discusses the training and testing stages, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the handling of occlusions, which could relate to the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The use of deep learning and the focus on learning from data without explicit supervision could also suggest the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.GR (Graphics).
